            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine the <strong>chopped chilli </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and <strong>tamarind paste </strong>in a small bowl with the juice of the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>orange</strong></p><p>Add your<strong> honey</strong>, <strong>soy sauce</strong>, <strong>rice vinegar</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>orange nam jim sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1690477257433-x200.jpg",
